WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.667 --> 00:00:04.534
♪♪

00:00:04.534 --> 00:00:08.400
♪♪

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:10.467
WE'RE ALL FAMILIAR
WITH THIS NEXT STORY.

00:00:10.467 --> 00:00:12.767
PICTURE ANY MOVIE
IN WHICH A HERO OR HEROINE

00:00:12.767 --> 00:00:14.400
IS RUNNING FROM A BAD GUY.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:18.300
THEY DUCK INTO A ROOM AND TRY
TO BARRICADE THE DOOR SHUT

00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:20.567
BY USING
THE FURNITURE THEY FIND.

00:00:20.567 --> 00:00:22.167
AND THIS IS OUR STORY.

00:00:22.167 --> 00:00:24.000
IS IT ACTUALLY FEASIBLE

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:26.400
TO BARRICADE AND MAKE A ROOM
IMPENETRABLE

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:29.367
WITH THE FURNITURE
YOU FIND IN THAT ROOM?

00:00:29.367 --> 00:00:32.534
THIS IS SUCH A CLASSIC
AND PERFECT MYTHBUSTERS MYTH --

00:00:32.534 --> 00:00:36.200
A STANDARD MOVIE TROPE BEING
PUT TO A RIGOROUS SET OF TESTS.

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:38.133
I CANNOT WAIT.

00:00:38.133 --> 00:00:42.434
YOUR 45 SECONDS START
IN THREE, TWO, ONE.

00:00:42.434 --> 00:00:44.000
ALL RIGHT.
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:47.801
Narrator:
IS IT POSSIBLE TO BARRICADE
A DOOR USING FURNITURE?

00:00:47.801 --> 00:00:49.501
HURRY UP, HURRY UP!

00:00:49.501 --> 00:00:51.634
IT'S A CLASSIC HOLLYWOOD SCENE,

00:00:51.634 --> 00:00:54.400
BUT IS IT REALLY FICTION?
GET 'EM!

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:57.767
THIS MYTHBUSTERS MOVIE MARATHON
IS DRAWING TO A CLOSE,

00:00:57.767 --> 00:01:00.734
AND HOW IT ENDS IS UP
TO THE BEAST OF THE BAY.

00:01:00.734 --> 00:01:03.901
-AH!
-NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

00:01:03.901 --> 00:01:05.701
Narrator:
BIG TOMMY TAKES HIS CUE.

00:01:05.701 --> 00:01:07.567
[ KNOCKS LOUDLY ]

00:01:07.567 --> 00:01:09.067
CHICKEN!

00:01:09.067 --> 00:01:12.868
♪♪

00:01:12.868 --> 00:01:14.801
[ SHOUTING ]

00:01:14.801 --> 00:01:19.667
♪♪

00:01:19.667 --> 00:01:22.934
AND AT THE END OF THE DAY,
TOMMY'S FORCE IS TOO GREAT

00:01:22.934 --> 00:01:27.200
FOR BOTH THE DOOR
AND THE FURNITURE STACK.

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.000
OH, MY GOD!

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:30.133
SOMEBODY ORDER PIZZA?

00:01:30.133 --> 00:01:31.834
[ LAUGHS ]

00:01:31.834 --> 00:01:34.100
THANK YOU, SIR.
THANK YOU.

00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:35.367
THAT WAS AWESOME.

00:01:35.367 --> 00:01:36.667
TOMMY, YOU ARE THE BEST.

00:01:36.667 --> 00:01:38.834
[ LAUGHING ]
YOU BROKE THE DOOR IN HALF.

00:01:38.834 --> 00:01:40.934
JUST TRYING
TO DELIVER PIZZA.

00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:42.334
AMAZING.

00:01:42.334 --> 00:01:44.267
ABSOLUTELY STUNNING.

00:01:44.267 --> 00:01:46.000
COULDN'T HAVE BEEN BETTER.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:47.701
OH, MY GOSH.

00:01:47.701 --> 00:01:51.767
Narrator: YEP, THE ACTION
MADE FOR A GREAT SCENE.

00:01:51.767 --> 00:01:54.200
BUT WITH SO MANY VARIABLES
AT PLAY,

00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:57.400
IS AN ALTERNATE SUCCESSFUL
ENDING POSSIBLE?

00:01:57.400 --> 00:02:00.467
BIG TOMMY WAS AMAZING
FOR THIS EXPERIMENT.

00:02:00.467 --> 00:02:02.400
I MEAN, JUST PERFECT,

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:05.400
BUT IT'S CLEAR THAT JESSE
AND RACHEL'S STRATEGY,

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:08.200
WHICH YOU SEE IN MOVIES ALL THE
TIME, WAS TOTALLY UNSUCCESSFUL.

00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:10.234
SO IF VALERIE AND I
ARE GONNA SUCCEED,

00:02:10.234 --> 00:02:12.033
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO COME UP
WITH SOMETHING

00:02:12.033 --> 00:02:13.367
TOTALLY DIFFERENT.

00:02:13.367 --> 00:02:16.367
I CAN BARELY WAIT.

00:02:16.367 --> 00:02:17.968
Narrator:
SO THE TEAMS SWITCH ROLES

00:02:17.968 --> 00:02:21.801
AND PREP FOR THE SECOND SET
OF ALTERNATIVE VARIABLES.

00:02:21.801 --> 00:02:24.367
I BROUGHT A PLANT.

00:02:24.367 --> 00:02:26.234
ALL RIGHT,
SO HERE'S THE SCENARIO.

00:02:26.234 --> 00:02:29.067
YOU ARE THE COUNTRY'S
NUMBER-TWO BOUNTY HUNTER.

00:02:29.067 --> 00:02:31.734
BEYOND THIS DOOR
IS THE FBI'S MOST WANTED.

00:02:31.734 --> 00:02:35.601
[ POLICE SIREN WAILING ]

00:02:35.601 --> 00:02:37.434
IF YOU GET
BEYOND THIS DOOR,

00:02:37.434 --> 00:02:39.534
YOU'LL BE NUMBER ONE.

00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:41.801
HMM.

00:02:41.801 --> 00:02:44.400
THESE DOORS DON'T STAND A CHANCE
AGAINST BIG TOMMY BURNS.

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.000
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.434
-LET'S GET IT.
-YEAH.

00:02:48.434 --> 00:02:52.100
Narrator: ADAM AND VALERIE
HAVE THEIR WORK CUT OUT.

00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:55.334
RACHEL AND JESSE HAVE PREPPED
A BEDROOM WITH CARPET FLOOR

00:02:55.334 --> 00:02:59.234
AND A NEW DOOR
FOR ADDED INTRUDER PROTECTION.

00:02:59.234 --> 00:03:00.634
TOMMY'S GONNA HAVE
TO GET THROUGH

00:03:00.634 --> 00:03:03.167
THE SOLID-CORE
INTERIOR DOOR NEXT.

00:03:03.167 --> 00:03:05.801
-ALL RIGHT.
-TA-DA.

00:03:05.801 --> 00:03:07.667
Narrator: CUE TAKE TWO.

00:03:07.667 --> 00:03:09.501
VALERIE AND ADAM,
ARE YOU READY?

00:03:09.501 --> 00:03:11.067
-READY!
-READY!

00:03:11.067 --> 00:03:12.501
ALL RIGHT.
FURNITURE BARRICADE.

00:03:12.501 --> 00:03:15.067
YOUR 45 SECONDS START...

00:03:15.067 --> 00:03:17.167
NOW.

00:03:17.167 --> 00:03:18.968
-RIGHT THIS WAY.
-THANK YOU.

00:03:18.968 --> 00:03:20.767
OKAY, HOLD ON, HOLD ON,
HOLD ON, ACTUALLY...

00:03:20.767 --> 00:03:24.334
Narrator: ADAM AND VALERIE
STRATEGICALLY PLACE THE SHELF...

00:03:24.334 --> 00:03:25.968
-30 SECONDS.
-YEP, TOTALLY.

00:03:25.968 --> 00:03:29.133
Narrator: ...THE SINGLE BED,

00:03:29.133 --> 00:03:31.868
A CHAIR, AND BEDSIDE,

00:03:31.868 --> 00:03:34.701
ALL END TO END
TO TRY TO JAM THE GAP

00:03:34.701 --> 00:03:37.167
BETWEEN THE OPPOSING WALL
AND THE DOOR.

00:03:37.167 --> 00:03:39.100
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:41.167
Narrator:
AND LEAVING NO STONE UNTURNED,

00:03:41.167 --> 00:03:43.801
THEY ADD THE DRESSER
FOR ADDITIONAL WEIGHT.

00:03:43.801 --> 00:03:45.100
HERE WE GO, HERE WE GO.
WATCH OUT.

00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:47.133
RIGHT UP AGAINST THERE.
THAT'S IT.

00:03:47.133 --> 00:03:48.467
DONE.

00:03:48.467 --> 00:03:50.667
Narrator: CUE BIG TOMMY.

00:03:54.501 --> 00:03:58.100
THE BARRICADE MAKES
AN IMPRESSIVE START

00:03:58.100 --> 00:03:59.801
AT KEEPING
THE BEAST AT BAY.

00:03:59.801 --> 00:04:01.601
-[ ROARS ]
-COME ON, TOMMY!

00:04:01.601 --> 00:04:04.634
-OH, MY GOD!
-OH, MY GOD.

00:04:04.634 --> 00:04:06.868
COME ON! GET IN!
COME ON!

00:04:06.868 --> 00:04:10.300
Narrator: THE DOOR IS SMASHED
INTO SMITHEREENS

00:04:10.300 --> 00:04:12.234
WHILE THE FURNITURE
HOLDS STRONG.

00:04:12.234 --> 00:04:13.601
YOU GOT THIS!

00:04:13.601 --> 00:04:15.467
BUT THE PAYOFF IS INEVITABLE.

00:04:17.367 --> 00:04:19.000
[ SHOUTING ]

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:20.367
HE'S IN!

00:04:20.367 --> 00:04:21.434
HE'S IN!

00:04:21.434 --> 00:04:23.868
[ LAUGHTER, CHEERING ]

00:04:23.868 --> 00:04:25.567
WOW.

00:04:25.567 --> 00:04:27.934
I AM SERIOUSLY,
TOTALLY WINDED.

00:04:27.934 --> 00:04:32.567
THAT ACTUALLY WORKED
FOR MOST OF THE TIME.

00:04:32.567 --> 00:04:35.300
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

00:04:35.300 --> 00:04:36.801
THAT WAS TERRIFYING.

00:04:36.801 --> 00:04:40.767
THAT DOOR IS ANNIHILATED,
COMPLETELY GONE.

00:04:40.767 --> 00:04:43.634
Narrator: THERE'S NO DOUBT
ABOUT THE HOLLYWOOD DRAMA,

00:04:43.634 --> 00:04:46.834
BUT WHAT ABOUT THE MYTH?

00:04:46.834 --> 00:04:48.934
ALL RIGHT, GUYS.
IT IS TIME TO CALL THIS MYTH,

00:04:48.934 --> 00:04:50.434
AND I'M GONNA POINT OUT,

00:04:50.434 --> 00:04:54.000
BIG TOMMY DID MAKE IT
THROUGH THE DOOR ON BOTH TESTS.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.100
YES, HE DID, BUT YOU
AND VALERIE'S TECHNIQUE

00:04:56.100 --> 00:04:58.067
OF BRACING FROM THE DOOR
TO THE OPPOSITE WALL

00:04:58.067 --> 00:05:00.934
WAS ACTUALLY REALLY EFFECTIVE,
AND IT ALMOST WORKED.

00:05:00.934 --> 00:05:04.400
AND CLEARLY, IT DEPENDS
ON THE DOOR, THE FURNITURE,

00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:05.868
AND THE SIZE OF THE ROOM.

00:05:05.868 --> 00:05:08.667
SO WHAT I'M HEARING IS,
THIS MYTH IS PLAUSIBLE.

00:05:08.667 --> 00:05:09.934
-PLAUSIBLE.
-PLAUSIBLE.

00:05:09.934 --> 00:05:12.901
-I THINK IT'S PLAUSIBLE.
-YEAH, IT'S PLAUSIBLE.

00:05:12.901 --> 00:05:13.901
-WHOA.
-THANKS, TOMMY, MAN.

00:05:13.901 --> 00:05:15.133
-THANKS, TOMMY.
-THANK YOU.

00:05:15.133 --> 00:05:16.534
-YOU'RE A CHAMPION.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

00:05:16.534 --> 00:05:19.501
Narrator:
YEP, THIS ONE'S NOT JUST
FOR THE SILVER SCREEN.

00:05:19.501 --> 00:05:22.868
GIVEN THE RIGHT CIRCUMSTANCES
AND SOME QUICK THINKING,

00:05:22.868 --> 00:05:27.200
A FURNITURE BARRICADE JUST
MIGHT LEAD TO A HAPPY ENDING.

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:29.634
♪♪

